laboratory_examinations.findings: MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.

Lung volumes remain low with crowding of bronchovascular markings, exaggeration of heart size, bilateral interstitial opacities likely representing mild pulmonary edema, and small bilateral pleural effusions may be slightly increased. No pneumothorax is seen.
